HEADWORD: Sporran
<hw>Spor"ran</hw> <pr>(sp⟦ocr⟧r"r⟦ait⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gael.
<ets>sporan</ets>.]</ety> <def>A large purse or pouch made of skin with
the hair or fur on, worn in front of the kilt by Highlanders when in
full dress.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

